response: "{ \"title\": \"Euler Totient Function\", \"description\": \"The Euler totient function counts the positive integers up to a given number n that are relatively prime to n. It is written as \u03c6(n) or \u2205(n). Write a function `euler_totient` that calculates the Euler totient function for a given integer n.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef euler_totient(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the value of the Euler totient function \u03c6(n).\\n\", \"code\": \"def euler_totient(n: int) -> int:\\n    result = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\\n        if gcd(i, n) == 1:\\n            result += 1\\n    return result\\n\\ndef gcd(a: int, b: int) -> int:\\n    while b != 0:\\n        a, b = b, a % b\\n    return abs(a)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert euler_totient(10) == 4\", \"assert euler_totient(1) == 1\", \"assert euler_totient(2) == 1\", \"assert euler_totient(3) == 2\"] }"
